task.summary: Default task
Added screenshots folder. Started to work on implementing graph construction for turn-based graphs (4 nodes at each intersection only permitting certain turn types).
Commented out the unfinished implementation of turn-based graph constructor
Added gif of real-time pathfinding
Added gif of real-time pathfinding
clockwise sort now working. about to delete prior buggy path distance code (that relied on buggy petgraph bellman-ford algorithm)
Made min_distance_all_points to isolate that feature as its own binary, then went through and removed all code unrelated to it.
Updated basic so it now produces a map just like shown on the github screenshot. Also removed all the unnecessary code from it. Made minor stylistic changes to other files.

Did significant work on the "right turns only graph". Currently the modified graph is constructed correctly, but I have not correctly implemented how to draw it to the screen (as there are now many duplicate edges for each road path)
Changed ReadMe to include overview section

Nearly complete with right_turns_only. The modified graph is built correctly, and I have a function to create a "difference graph", but I need to write the function that takes the min distance info and transforms into an Undirected graph

Have written the function that takes the min-distance data and the modified graph and creates a simpler graph with just undirected edges representing average min distance of the end points. Started adding tests for this as this program as these functions are definitely non-trivial. Am also about to delete some unnecessary stuff at the bottom of the file I had forgotten about.
About to try redoing it, as I need to better handle cases like 2 and 3 way intersections, and it's easier to redo the modified graph construction again.

attempting to make a trait object for road nodes, where it internally figures out for each road node how it should penalize/connect incoming edges with outgoing. Might be different one for different cases, and default value for cases I don't think of.
Deleted my prior version of prohibit_left_turns / FourWay object. Made tests for sort_clockwise and the graph isomorph algorithm.

sort_clockwise(...) now works and passes test. Made some of the basic tests for the modified graph construction (they do not pass yet). Have now decided that for simplicity sake we will allow penalties for left,straight, and right, but there will be NO u-turns because it's not a very interesting case and it greatly complicates the graph tests (which are crazy complicated as it is).

About to totally redo the turns project, making the modified graph be based on the ideas of lanes (two lanes for a road), as this will hopefully be much more conceptually simple and easier to reason about, although it will make even more complicated test cases.

The new method (of using lanes) is now mostly implemented. Simple graphs now work correctly, but fourways and T-Intersections do not. I'm about to delete all the old test cases for the prior method (but were commented out).
All tests now work (including fourway clone graph), but I haven't tested yet with other components (min distance, etc.). About to delete some unused methods/testcases (sort_clone_list)

Everything now works (including drawing to the screen)! It currrently only deals with fourway intersections and other forms of intersections are ignored, but everything is together. About to do some refactoring to simplify everything.
